description
the nielsen company is the largest global measurement company in the world with unique measurement technology asset and data that make it one of the most interesting and challenging place for a measurement or data scientist to work we focus on what consumer watch listen to and buy in over 95 country
data science is core to what nielsen doe and our research project have high visibility in directly impacting the result of our business and our client this position is in the research methods team within nielsens data science organization the research methods team provides leadership and expertise across nielsen to develop innovative statistically sound and cost effective research methodology in support of the strategic business initiative we play a pivotal role in designing best practice and approach for data collection respondent recruitment and panelist retention
job purpose
work with cross-functional team to design implement and test new audience measurement methodology
identify and implement method and best practice to improve respondent cooperation and retention especially among hard-to-reach population eg hispanics asians young adult
lead the design and testing of data collection methodology for nielsen panel and survey
provide support for technical guidance and training of nielsen operational team including call center and in-person field recruitment team
serve a subject matter expert for panel recruitment and compliance methodology incorporating industry knowledge and best practice into design and recommendation
responsibilities
lead multiple complex cross-functional research project
direct research planning and budget for various methodology evaluation and test
use both qualitative and quantitative method to improve survey method and recruitment approach
balance cost quality and schedule requirement to design measurement method and approach adapt a needed
correspond and communicate with key internal stakeholder and external supplier communicate research finding and recommendation effectively use judgement to prioritize and modify recommendation a needed manager project requirement and schedule
conduct usability research to develop and evaluate web mobile application and other electronic material
estimate research development cost for project budget
stay abreast of procedural and technological development in survey and measurement research methodology and changing technology in the marketplace proactively identify application of these latest development to improve existing method
provide consultation on methodological and procedural factor that impact respondent cooperation and data quality such a questionnaire design and survey mode effect
manage and analyze complex survey panel data including developing data file conducting quality review data editing documentation weighting and imputation
author technical proposal report and article present research to internal stakeholder and at research conference
qualifications
required qualifications
masters degree or phd in social or behavioral social sciences field such a survey methodology statistics sampling psychology sociology or related field with 5 year research experience or bachelors degree with 7 year experience
knowledge of survey or similar research operation including questionnaire design cognitive interview sampling and survey administration
knowledge of multiple mode of data collection method including online and mobile survey
knowledge of mixed-mode survey design and panel recruitment and maintenance
ability to design sound methodology within cost and operational constraint understanding of measurement error in data collection method with ability to mitigate using cost effective procedure
high motivation with demonstrated capacity to work on multiple project with set deadline under pressure
collaborative team player with willingness and desire to work with global cross-functional team of varying size
creative aptitude and ability and desire to explore opportunity for new research innovation
excellent oral and written communication skill required for presenting to and collaborating with group of diverse background
ability to explain complex research concept to individual without a survey research background
qualitative research and analysis skill including cognitive interview in-depth interview focus group etc
quantitative research and analysis skill including competence with statistical software python or r preferred
experience with google suite docs sheets slides etc
desired qualifications
proficiency in non-english language spanish or mandarin preferred and understanding of multiple culture
knowledge of advanced cognitive or behavioral methodology eg eye tracking
knowledge of large-scale complex multi-stage survey in market research or government setting
